commitResults.messageTitle: Format code to Java coding standard.

commitResults.messageBody:
Added loadData, appendTaskToFile, saveTaskListToFile, methods to allow
for saving and loading of the tasklist from the disk.

Added removeCorruptedData method to handle deletion of incorrect data at
the loadData stage. The method is designed to to only take an array of
indexes to allow for flexibility in what thrown exceptions are picked up
to be removed and to allow for deletion of larger numbers of corrupted
entries in a single pass.

Modified main method to use switch statement for todo, deadline and
event commands for better code readability.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Deadline, Event and Duke classes.
commitResults.messageBody:
Updated Deadline and Event to store date as LocalDateTime.
Updated Deadline and Event getDate and getData methods to output the
correct date format.

Updated Duke with parseDate method to convert string in dd/MM/yyyy HHmm
format to LocalDateTime object.

commitResults.messageTitle: Update Deadline, Event and Duke classes
commitResults.messageBody:
Updated Deadline and Event to store date as LocalDateTime.
Updated Deadline and Event getDate and getData methods to output the
correct date format.

Updated Duke with parseDate method to convert string in dd/MM/yyyy HHmm
format to LocalDateTime object.

Split Duke class functionality into multiple subclasses.

TaskList class added to handle editing of current tasklist within the
program.

Storage class added to handle reading and writing of tasklist data to
hard disk.

Parser class added to handle interpreting of user input commands.

Ui class added to handle displaying of information.

Command abstract class and subclasses added to handle multiple possible
user commands in a streamlined manner within the main program loop.

Multiple minor edits made to Javadoc comments and formatting

commitResults.messageTitle: Initial package restructure for better code organization
commitResults.messageBody:
Added packages for duke, duke.task and duke.command.

Fixed TaskList(ArrayList) constructor bug where taskCount was not initialised leading to
incorrect reading and writing to file.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove unwanted test files and data directory
Add Junit tests for Parser and Event Classes

commitResults.messageBody:
Added additional logic to Parser class to handle find command inputs.
Added corresponding FindCommand class to handle execution of the find
command.
Added corresponding findTasks method to TaskList class for OOP-compliant
searching for matches.

Added new methods to Ui to allow for handling of printing lists to the
console. Modified ListCommand to utilise the new Ui method.

commitResults.messageTitle: Clean up code to follow Java Coding Standards
Fix bug displaying 1. for all list elements

commitResults.messageBody:
Add .xml files for gradle checkstyle under config/checkstyle/ dir.

Cleaned up all syntax errors in code across multiple classes.

Removed erroneous merge conflict messages that were found in javadocs.

Changed Command and all subclasses to return a String for GUI to
display in addition to printing to the console.

Rectified bug in Storage and Tasklist instantiation and updating that
caused both private tasks arraylists to reference the same object
causing double updates to be displayed when adding tasks.

Added Launcher, Main, MainWindow and DialogBox classes to manage the
GUI.Also added DialogBox and MainWindow fxml files. Added images for
user and bot.

commitResults.messageTitle: Enforce adherence to style guide for tests
commitResults.messageBody:
Reorganised imports and edited code for ParserTest and EventTest classes
to pass checkstyle automated testing.
